@startuml sie-governance-loop-v1

' ============================================================
' VISUAL THEME
' ============================================================

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 12
skinparam ArrowColor #57606A
skinparam DefaultFontName "SansSerif"
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF

skinparam componentBackgroundColor #F6F8FA
skinparam componentBorderColor #57606A

skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF8C5
skinparam noteBorderColor #57606A

title SIE - Closed-Loop Governance Architecture - v1

' ============================================================
' CONTROL THEORY MODEL
' ============================================================

note as ControlNote
  **Control Theory Applied to System Governance**
  
  SIE implements a closed-loop control system:
  
  1. **Desired State**: Policies define what "good" looks like
  2. **Measured State**: Collectors observe actual system state
  3. **Error Signal**: Violations = gap between desired and actual
  4. **Controller**: Behavioral rules compute corrections
  5. **Actuator**: Agents apply remediations to State Plane
  6. **Feedback**: Results feed back to refine future actions
  
  This is the same pattern as:
  - Kubernetes reconciliation loops
  - Thermostats (temperature control)
  - PID controllers (industrial automation)
end note

' ============================================================
' THE LOOP
' ============================================================

rectangle "Desired State\n(Policies & Constraints)" as DesiredState #D4EDDA {
  [Functional Policies]
  [Viability Policies]
  [Structural Policies]
  [Behavioral Rules]
}

rectangle "Comparator\n(Policy Evaluator)" as Comparator #E8E8F4 {
  [CEL Runtime] as CEL
  [Violation Detector] as ViolationDetector
}

rectangle "Measured State\n(State Store)" as MeasuredState #F4E8E8 {
  [Current System State]
  [Historical State]
  [Metrics & Telemetry]
}

rectangle "Controller\n(Behavioral Rule Engine)" as Controller #E8F4E8 {
  [Rule Matcher]
  [Action Selector]
  [Remediation Planner]
}

rectangle "Actuator\n(Enforcement Agents)" as Actuator #F6F8FA {
  [Config Actuator]
  [Scaling Actuator]
  [Deployment Actuator]
  [Alert Actuator]
}

rectangle "State Plane\n(Customer Systems)" as StatePlane #F0F8FF {
  [Kubernetes]
  [Cloud Resources]
  [Applications]
  [Infrastructure]
}

rectangle "Sensor\n(State Collectors)" as Sensor #F6F8FA {
  [Event Collector]
  [Metric Collector]
  [Config Collector]
  [Inventory Collector]
}

' ============================================================
' LOOP CONNECTIONS
' ============================================================

DesiredState -down-> Comparator : reference\ninput
MeasuredState -up-> Comparator : measured\ninput
Comparator -right-> Controller : error signal\n(violations)
Controller -down-> Actuator : control\nactions
Actuator -down-> StatePlane : apply\nchanges
StatePlane -left-> Sensor : system\nstate
Sensor -up-> MeasuredState : state\nupdates

' ============================================================
' FEEDBACK PATHS
' ============================================================

rectangle "Feedback Analysis" as Feedback #FFF8C5 {
  [Trend Analysis]
  [Effectiveness Tracking]
  [Pattern Learning]
}

Actuator -right-> Feedback : action\nresults
Feedback -up-> Controller : tuning\nrecommendations
Feedback -left-> DesiredState : policy\nrefinements

' ============================================================
' HUMAN IN THE LOOP
' ============================================================

actor "Governance\nOfficer" as Human

Human -down-> DesiredState : define\npolicies
Human -right-> Controller : approve\nactions
Human -down-> Feedback : review\neffectiveness

note right of Human
  **Human Oversight**
  - Policy definition
  - Exception approval
  - Escalation handling
  - Continuous improvement
end note

' ============================================================
' TIMING ANNOTATIONS
' ============================================================

note bottom of Comparator
  **Evaluation Frequency**
  - Continuous: Event-driven
  - Periodic: Batch scans
  - On-demand: API requests
  
  **Latency Target**
  < 100ms for critical paths
end note

note bottom of Controller
  **Action Types**
  - Immediate: Auto-heal
  - Queued: Batch remediation
  - Deferred: Human approval
  - Preventive: Pre-deployment gate
end note

note bottom of StatePlane
  **State Plane**
  Customer systems that:
  - Source state (→ Description Plane)
  - Are operated (← Remediation Plane)
  - Are modeled in CSDM schemas
end note

' ============================================================
' LOOP CHARACTERISTICS
' ============================================================

legend bottom
  |= Property |= Value |
  | Loop Type | Negative feedback (error-correcting) |
  | Stability | Damped oscillation → equilibrium |
  | Gain | Configurable per rule severity |
  | Deadband | Configurable thresholds to avoid chatter |
  | Rate Limiting | Prevents rapid oscillation |
endlegend

@enduml
